Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded Bethlehem Steel Corp's debt securities.    Bethlehem has one billion dlrs of debt and preferred stockoutstanding. Cut were its senior debt to CCC-plus from B-minusand subordinated debt to CCC-minus from CCC. S and P affirmedthe C-rated preferred, since preferred dividends werediscontinued last year.     S and P cited concerns over Bethlehem's viability over theintermediate term, rather than any immediate threat tosolvency. Its cash is strong relative to 1987 requirements, butwas accumulated through such means as asset sales. Reuter&#3;